Lisp:tail.el is a small interface for the unix tool tail.

<b>Note:</b> Emacs 22 and later includes auto-revert-tail-mode and do not require the Unix tail utility.  To enable in a buffer, use <code>M-x auto-revert-tail-mode</code>.

== Configuration ==

Put tail.el in your <code>load-path</code> and this in your .emacs file:

 (require 'tail)

Alternatively you can use <code>autoload</code> (replace <code><path></code> with to local path):

 (autoload 'tail-file "<path>/tail.el" "Tail a file." t)
 (autoload 'tail-command "<path>/tail.el" "Tail a file with arguments." t)

== Screenshot ==

Using the <code>tail-file</code> command with /var/log/syslog:

